  "prompt": "What is the processing time for Australian Visa 190?",
  "response": "The processing time for an Australian **Subclass 190 (Skilled Nominated) Visa** can vary depending on several factors, including the completeness of your application, the volume of applications being processed, and the specific circumstances of your case. Generally, the Department of Home Affairs provides estimated processing times for visa applications, which are updated regularly.\n\n### **Current Processing Times for Subclass 190 Visa (as of October 2023):**\n- **75% of applications:** Processed within **7 months**\n- **90% of applications:** Processed within **8 months**\n\nThese are approximate timelines and can change based on individual circumstances, such as additional document requests or health and character checks.\n\n### **Factors Affecting Processing Time:**\n1. Accuracy and completeness of your application.\n2. Response time to requests for additional information.\n3. Priority given to certain occupations (if applicable).\n4. Health and character clearance delays.\n5. Processing capacity of the Department of Home Affairs.\n\n### **Tips to Minimize Delays:**\n- Ensure all documents are submitted correctly and meet the requirements.\n- Respond promptly to any requests for additional information.\n- Apply for health and character checks early.\n\nIt\u2019s always a good idea to check the **Department of Home Affairs website** for the most up-to-date processing times and guidelines.",
